parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defects in the transmission can cause the vehicle to suddenly downshift, lose power, or fail to stay in park, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly downshifts
loses power
or fails to stay in park
causing the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent loss of power can cause the vehicle to stall or lose acceleration, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls
or runs rough
often accompanied by a flashing check engine icon.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle to stay in park can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or damage.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to stay in park
rolling or moving forward even when the shifter is in the "P" position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical issues can cause unexpected behavior, such as the radio turning on randomly or the tailgate opening on its own, which can be distracting and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The radio turns on randomly
the tailgate opens on its own
or other unexpected electrical behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The distorted or blank rear-view camera screen can reduce the driver's visibility, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries when reversing.
symptoms: The rear-view camera screen displays a distorted image or a blank screen intermittently while reversing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shut-off of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioner shuts off immediately after being turned on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Blower Motor Speed Control Electrical Connection Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower motor speed control electrical connection can cause the air conditioner blower to stop working, leading to discomfort and distraction to the driver.
symptoms: The air conditioner blower stops working
and the electrical connection at the blower motor speed control may be burned or damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Conditioning System Failure with Fire Risk
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause a fire, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even death.
symptoms: The air conditioning system becomes inoperable
smoke comes through the air vents
fire appears from under the glove box.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or even death, especially in situations where pedestrians are present.
symptoms: The engine surges
the vehicle propels forward without warning
loss of control over the vehicle.
